Rule 17g-7 Rating Disclosure
The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) requires that all nationally statistical rating 
          organizations (NRSRO) such as Egan-Jones Ratings Company to make available to the public a history of all 
          the obligors/issuers that were rated by the NRSRO within 12 months of the rating action date for credit ratings paid for
		  by the obligor or issuer and within 24 months of the rating action date for all other credit ratings. Below is a zip file containing 
          all of the obligors and issuers that were rated by Egan-Jones in XBRL format.
      
Download 17g-7 Disclosure XBRL File





